Maiharaji Altine, Gusau The Chairman of Zamfara State chapter of the Peoples Democratic Party, Alhaji Ibrahim Mallaha, is dead. Aged 57, Mallaha reportedly died in a private hospital in Germany in the early hours of Monday after a protracted illness. Mallaha was an active politician in Zamfara, who served as the chairman of the defunct ANPP before defecting to the PDP along with former governor Mahmuda Aliyu Shinkafi. He was survived by four wives and many children. The PDP Publicity Secretary, Alhaji Faruku Rijiya, described Mallahaâ€™s death as a great loss. Copyright PUNCH.
